  - STATE_UPDATE: {'last_reflection_result': '## Post-Mortem Analysis Summary\n\n**Attempt 3, Round 1**\n\n### Solved Problems\nNone yet - this is the first analysis round.\n\n### Unsolved Problems\n**Step 1 (Build) FAILED** - Compilation error due to `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay incompatibility with Go 1.25.7.\n\nThe root cause is:\n- The project uses **Go 1.25.7** (from `go.mod`)\n- `go-118-fuzz-build` creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go` in the Go toolchain\n- In Go 1.25+, the toolchain is stored under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`)\n- Go\'s overlay mechanism explicitly **forbids** replacing files under `GOMODCACHE`\n- Error: `"Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced."`\n\n### Deterioration Score: **5** (Stagnant)\n- Step 1 (Build) failed - compilation error\n- Steps 2 and 6 not reached\n- First analysis round, no regression from previous state\n\n### Backtracking Check: **No rollback needed**\n- Complexity Overload: No fix applied yet\n- Logical Loop: First entry in journal\n- Strategy Exhaustion: First attempt\n- High Deterioration: Score 5 (≤ 7)\n\n### Recommended Fix Direction\nThe fix needs to address the `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay mechanism. Options include:\n1. **Patch `go-118-fuzz-build`** to skip the overlay for `testing/fuzz.go` when the toolchain is under GOMODCACHE\n2. **Modify `build.sh`** to use a different approach for fuzzing that doesn\'t trigger this overlay issue\n3. **Set environment variables** to relocate the toolchain outside GOMODCACHE'}
