  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': "The HAFix analysis is complete. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## HAFix Root Cause Analysis Complete\n\n### Phase 1-3: Dynamic Clue Mining & Chain-of-Evidence Synthesis\n\n**Error Analysis:**\nThe build fails with:\n```\ngo: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\n```\n\n### Phase 4: Attribution Decision\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Suspect SHA** | `1d5755d81c5fb00218f04925b5dbc2f312749547` |\n| **Commit Message** | `fix(deps): update module github.com/hashicorp/vault/sdk to v0.25.1` |\n| **What it changed** | Bumped Go version from `1.25.0` → `1.25.7` in `go.mod` |\n| **Root Cause Chain** | Go 1.25+ stores the toolchain as a module under GOMODCACHE. The `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay mechanism tries to replace `testing/fuzz.go` in the toolchain, but Go forbids overlay replacements under GOMODCACHE. |\n| **Attribution** | **DOWNSTREAM** - This is an OSS-Fuzz infrastructure/build configuration issue, not a source code bug. The fix should be in the OSS-Fuzz project config (build.sh/Dockerfile) to work around the Go 1.25+ toolchain module behavior. |\n| **Target Fix Path** | `/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager/` |\n| **Key Evidence** | The `go.mod` diff shows `-go 1.25.0` → `+go 1.25.7`. The build log shows the overlay error referencing the toolchain under GOMODCACHE. |"}
