  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': "The HAFix analysis is complete. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## HAFix Root Cause Analysis Complete\n\n### Suspect SHA: `1d5755d81c5fb00218f04925b5dbc2f312749547`\n\n**Root Cause Chain:**\nCommit `1d5755d81` (Apr 7, 2026) bumped `go.mod` from `go 1.25.0` to `go 1.25.7`. In Go 1.25+, when the `go.mod` specifies a Go version that differs from the installed Go version, Go auto-downloads the matching toolchain as a module under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/`). The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go` in GOROOT, but since GOROOT now points to a path under GOMODCACHE, Go's overlay mechanism rejects it.\n\n**Attribution: DOWNSTREAM** (Config/Infrastructure issue)\n\n**Target Fix Path:** `/home/senchen/temp/fix_build_agent/oss-fuzz/projects/cert-manager/`\n\n**Key Evidence:**\n- Build log error: `go: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.`\n- Commit `1d5755d81` changed `go 1.25.0` → `go 1.25.7` in `go.mod`\n- Container diagnostic shows `GOROOT=/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64` (under GOMODCACHE)\n- File `/root/.go/src/testing/fuzz.go` exists outside GOMODCACHE and can be used as the overlay target\n\n**Fix Strategy:** Set `export GOROOT=/root/.go` in `build.sh` to redirect the overlay target away from GOMODCACHE."}
